<DOCNO> XIE19980731.0005 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Vietnam Hit by Severe Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Central Vietnam is suffering from a
severe drought, local reports said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Some 55,000 hectares of rice in five central provinces will be
damaged by the drought if no rain comes in the next 10 days.
</P>
<P>
Ten thousand hectares of rice, 3,000 hectares of subsidiary
food crops and 4,000 hectares of short-term industrial crops in
the region have already died.
</P>
<P>
The drought is a result of continuous dry weather from early
June and a long hot spell from July 15, with temperatures staying
over 38 degrees celsius in the region and reaching 41 degrees
celsius in some places.
</P>
<P>
More than 1.1 million local inhabitants are suffering from
serious shortages of water for daily use. Water has to be
transported by tanks to some localities.
</P>
<P>
Water levels in rivers and reservoirs in the region have
dropped below the dead level, with some rivers having dried up.
</P>
<P>
Government officials have inspected the situation in the
hardest hit provinces and discussed with local administrations
solutions to reduce the losses.
</P>
<P>
They agreed to give priority to supplying water for domestic
use and saving the farm areas that still have a chance to
survive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
