<HEADLINE> 14 killed in Road Accident in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen people including nine
women were killed and 15 others injured Thursday in a road
accident in central Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place near Sadiq Nihung, about 40 kilometers
south Jhang in Pakistan's eastern province of Punjab, according to
a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
A wagon heading to Shorkot, about 75 kilometers south in Jhang,
collided with a loaded stationary trailer due to overspeeding,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
Most of the passengers died on the spot and the injured have
been sent to a hospital, the report said. 
</P>
