<HEADLINE> Figure of Unemployed S. Africans Great: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A total of 29.5 percent of
the labor force in South Africa are unemployed, Labor Minister
Shepherd Mdladlana quoted a survey by the Central Statistical
Services as saying Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The figure of unemployment included those who are not actively
looking for work, Mdladlana said in a written reply to a
parliamentary question from the opposition National Party.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the South African government was planning
to reduce unemployment through a job summit due to be held later
this year, at which discussions would be held to find a way out
to promote employment.
</P>
<P>
The policies and programs of the government's employment
strategy would also be used to bring about employment in a
coherent, co-ordinated and effective manner, the minister said.
</P>
