<HEADLINE> UAE to Send Relief Supplies to War-Stricken Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates Red
Crescent Society RCC has decided to send relief supplies to Sudan
soon, the RCC told reporters today.
</P>
<P>
The RCC is preparing medical supplies, as part of the relief
aid, for three Sudanese hospitals to improve the therapeutical
conditions there, said the RCC.
</P>
<P>
It added that also included is 160 tonnes of food that would be
sent by air to help those suffering from famine in the civil
war-stricken southern part of the African state.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese government and the rebel group Sudanese People
Liberation Army declared a ceasefire, apparently in order to
facilitate the accessibility of relief materials.
</P>
<P>
Some 2.5 million people in Sudan are suffering from famine, and
lack of medicine and potable water as a result of the 15-year-old
civil war in the country.
</P>
<P>
The UAE is keen on offering financial and material aid for the
Arab and Muslim nations in need, the RCC said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
