<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Puts Priority on Coop with South: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Malaysian President
Mahathir Mohammed said Thursday his government has decided to put
priority on cooperations with the developing countries as an
approach to dealing with the crisis facing Asia.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said this at the opening ceremony here of a new
Malaysian bank, the International Commercial Bank, in Maputo.
</P>
<P>
The financial cooperation between Malaysia and Mozambique has
shrunken in the wake of the crisis in Southeast Asia, Mahathir
noted, adding that the two countries will surely find better ways
to push forward their cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian president believed that the financial crisis
across East Asia has been the result of the selfishness and
indifference of the rich and industrialized nations, which frown
on South-South cooperation among the developing nations.
</P>
<P>
At the inauguration of the new Malaysian bank, Mozambican
President Joaquim Chissano pointed out that the opening of the
the Bank has demonstrated the confidence of the Malaysian
entrepreneurs, and financiers in particular, in the future
development of the Mozambican politics and economy.
</P>
<P>
Chissano hoped that the bank will operate beyond the capital
Maputo to better serve the Mozambican people.
</P>
<P>
He also called on the potential investors both at home and
abroad and other business people to actively participate in the
development of this southern African country.
</P>
<P>
Since September 1997 when Mahathir paid a visit to Mozambique,
the Malaysian investment started coming into Mozambique and
cooperation between industrialists of the two nations has been
strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the large number of private industrialists who
"are accompanying me in this visit," the Malaysian president
said, "they are paving the way for their return to the region
after the Asian crisis."
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the direct trade between Mozambique and
Malaysia is less than 10 million U.S. Dollars per year.
</P>
<P>
However, the Mozambican officials believe that through
Mahathir's visit and the efforts of both sides, the trade volume
between the two nations will expand up to 50 million U.S.
Dollars in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir arrived here Wednesday afternoon for a three-day
visit to Mozambique after attending the second Southern African
International Dialog which was aimed at generating wealth through
the smart partnerships. 
