<HEADLINE> Investment Contract Inked Between Coca-Cola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government and the
U.S. Coca-Cola Corporation signed an investment contract worth 36
million U.S. Dollars here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the contract, the two sides will jointly
establish a joint venture in Angola with 45 percent of the
capital provided by the Angolan government and 55 percent by
Coca-Cola.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will be located in Bengo Province, 60
kilometers away from the capital city Luanda. The construction
of the enterprise will start in November and be completed in
November next year with an initial capacity of two million boxes
(24 bottles of beverage in each box).
</P>
<P>
Angolan Minister of Industry Manuel Dugue told the press after
the signing ceremony that this is Angola's biggest project in the
industrial sector these years and it will help to prompt the
social and economic development in the war-ravaged southern
African country.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Treasury Minister Alcantara Monteiro said that the
contract is the fruit of the four-year long negotiations between
the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Secretary-General of the Angolan Treasury Ministry Rui
Carreira signed on the contract with David Lyons, Coca-Cola's
Africa Chief in the presence of Angolan ministers of planning,
state administration and employment and other officials. 
