<HEADLINE> EU Industrial Production Up 1.3 Pct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The 15-nation European Union
registered a 1.3-percent increase in industrial production between
February and April this year, Eurostat reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical bureau of the European
communities said that the 11-country euro zone also posted an
industrial production increase of 1.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Germany and France, both long-time locomotives of the European
Union economy, led the growth trend with 1.8 percent and 1.6
percent respectively, followed by Portugal and Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Austria, Britain and Italy, however, had little change from the
previous three-month period whereas a strong growth was apparent
in Portugal at 1.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
EU-wide, the production of capital goods was up 2.4 percent;
intermediate goods up 1.1 percent; consumer durables up 1.6
percent and consumer non-durables up 0.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Germany and France also led the upward trend in the production
of capital goods, intermediate goods and consumer durables.
</P>
<P>
Germany and France both had growth well above the EU average.
</P>
<P>
Denmark was the only European Union member state that had a
negative growth of minus 6.2 percent against the EU average.

nnnn
02:49  02:49
</P>
<P>
