<DOCNO> XIE19980731.0033 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Finances Creation of 33 Energy Agencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission announced
on Thursday that it is funding the creation and first three years
of operation of 33 energy agencies in Europe.
</P>
<P>
These energy agencies, 16 regional and 17 urban ones, will each
benefit from an EU funding of 150,000 ECU (165,000 U.S. dollars),
totalling 4.95 million ECU (5.44 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The new additions will bring the total of European
Commission-financed energy agencies to 173.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the regional and urban energy agency
management is to define and implement a series of activities aimed
at improving demand management by promoting energy efficiency and
at ensuring better use of local and renewable resources while
facilitating growing awareness among local policy-makers of the
impact of energy on those other policies for which they are
responsible.
</P>
<P>
The energy agencies are expected to contribute to better
community integration in energy matters through a bottom-up
approach to energy problems, to boost the efforts of the regional
and local entities involved in the efforts to combat climate
change and to foster economic and social cohesion by reducing the
disparities between regions.
</P>
<P>
Of the 33 new energy agencies, one will be set up for the first
time in Norway that, along side Iceland, is a European Economic
Area country that is entitled to submit proposals and participate
on terms similar to those of the European Union member states in
EU energy programs.
</P>
<P>
The energy agencies will cooperate with one another and will
draw on the experience of the existing agencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
