<HEADLINE> Israeli Soldier Killed, 4 Wounded in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 30 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli soldier was killed and
four others wounded Thursday in south Lebanon by a roadside bomb,
Lebanon's Orient radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The bomb blew up when an Israeli patrol passed by the village
of Rihan in the eastern sector of the Israeli-occupied area, the
radio said.
</P>
<P>
The Hezbollah, or Party of God, has claimed responsibility for
the attack, saying that one of its units detonated the bomb.
</P>
<P>
The fresh death toll raised to nine the number of Israeli
soldiers killed in south Lebanon this year, during which some 23
Hezbollah guerrillas have also been killed.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a 1,200-square-kilometer security zone in south
Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its northern
towns from cross-border attacks by Lebanese guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
The Hezbollah is leading a guerrilla war against 1,500 Israeli
troops and 2,500 Israeli-allied South Lebanon Army militia in the
self-styled security zone.
</P>
<P>
In April, Israel offered to withdraw from south Lebanon under
the condition that Lebanese government guarantee the security of
Israel's border areas.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon has rejected the proposal, insisting that the
withdrawal be unconditional, as called for by the United Nations
Security Council Resolution 425 approved 20 years ago. 
</P>
