<HEADLINE> Backstedt Wins 19th Stage in Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Magnus Backstedt of Sweden won a
four-man sprint to the line to take out Friday's 19th stage of the
Tour de France cycle race, a 242-kilometer ride from La
Chaux-de-Fonds in Switzerland to Autun, France.
</P>
<P>
Backstedt edged out Martin Den Bakker of the Netherlands, Eddy
Mazzoleni of Italy and Pascal Derame of France in the final dash
for the line.
</P>
<P>
He clocked five hours 10 minutes and 14 seconds as he won a
stage of the race in his first year riding in the Tour and became t
he first Swede to win a stage.
</P>
<P>
Marco Pantani of Italy retained the overall leaders' yellow
stage with just two days left to the finish in Paris on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Pantani will go into the final two stages with a lead of five
minutes and 42 seconds over second-placed American Bobby Julich
and 5:56 over third-placed Jan Ullrich of Germany.
</P>
<P>
Only 14 of the 21 teams that began the blighted Tour remained
and only 87 riders -- less than half the original field --
remained at the start of the largely flat stage.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's penultimate stage is a 52-km time trial between
Montceau-Les-Mines and Le Creusot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
