<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast Kills 3 in Algiers Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- In the second terror attack in two
days, a bomb blast ripped through a market in Algiers Friday
morning, leaving three dead and 23 others injured.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities said that the bomb exploded in the crowded
market near Kouba, in the southern outskirts of the capital.
</P>
<P>
After the blast, Interior Minister Mustefa Benmansour rushed to
the site accompanied by local police and officials.
</P>
<P>
Police combed the area to conduct investigation into the blast,
for which no one has claimed responsibility.
</P>
<P>
This was the second blast in Algiers in the past two days after
a bomb blew up a bus in a suburb of the capital Thursday, killing
one passenger and wounding 13 others.
</P>
<P>
The bombings were launched at a time when a United Nations
fact-finding mission is currently in the violence-torn country to
seek ways of settling the six years of Islamic insurgency.
</P>
<P>
Over 75,000 people, mostly civilians, have been killed since
1992 when Islamic militants launched terror attacks to protest the
government's cancellation of the parliamentary elections in which
an Islamic party was expected to win. 
</P>
