<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Plays Important Role In Fighting Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Over the last few days, nearly
four million Chinese soldiers, armed police, and reserve military
personnel took part in the battle against the flooding in central
and eastern provinces along the Yangtze River, official sources
say.
</P>
<P>
These personnel have helped move more than 300,000 people to
safer ground and 100,000 tons of goods in flooded areas to safer
places.
</P>
<P>
The military and armed police troops participating in the
effort were under the command of 44 generals and over 1,400
division and regiment commanders.
</P>
<P>
Local governments have also cooperated by seeing to it that
there was adequate food, medicines, and lodging for the soldiers.
</P>
<P>
In many flood hit places, servicemen were charged lower rates
for taxi rides or for making phone calls. 
</P>
