<HEADLINE> China Offers Zimbabwe $25.5M in Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government Friday
decided to provide a preferential loan and a grant amounting to
210 million Chinese Yuan (about 25.2 million U.S. Dollars) to
Zimbabwe to finance Chinese-aided projects in the country.
</P>
<P>
This was contained in the framework agreement on the provision
of a preferential loan signed here Friday by Deputy Minister of
the Chinese Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Ministry Sun
Guanxiang and Deputy Minister of the Zimbabwean Finance Ministry
Misheck Chinamasa.
</P>
<P>
