<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Discovers 8,891 HIV Carriers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has discovered 8,891 HIV
(Human Immunodeficiency Virus) carriers nationwide, the Vietnamese
News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to Vietnam's national AIDS committee, as many as
1,211 people had developed full-blown cases of AIDS and 648 had
died of the disease by July 15.
</P>
<P>
The northern coastal province of Quang Ninh is reported to have
the highest rate of HIV positive carriers, about 67.2 cases per
100,000 persons.
</P>
<P>
It is followed by the northern province of Lang Son with 60.9
cases per 100,000 persons, and Ho Chi Minh city with 59.2 cases
per 100,000 persons.
</P>
<P>
Persons under the age of 39 make up a major part of the HIV
carriers, with 32.35 percent of them being drug addicts and 13.24
percent being sex workers, according to an analysis made by the
aids committee.
</P>
<P>
The committee considers education the most important measure to
prevent the spread of AIDS in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
