<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Province Trying For 10 Percent Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province
is increasing efforts to have a 10 percent economic growth rate
this year, two percentage points higher than the national target.
</P>
<P>
In the first half, the province had 347.6 billion yuan (42
billion U.S. dollars) in gross domestic product, a year-on-year
growth of 9.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Lu Ruihua, Guangdong's governor, told a provincial meeting that
to reach this goal, exports need to be increased, high-tech
businesses developed, infrastructure and housing construction
increased, and tourism developed.
</P>
<P>
The governor especially emphasized the importance of increased
exports and asked that an all-out effort be made.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong accounts for more than 40 percent of the country's
total foreign trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
