<HEADLINE> Nigerian Tests Positive at Basketball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian center Julius Nwosu has
tested positive for the banned substance ephedrine, international
basketball federation officials said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nwosu, 27, tested positive after Nigeria's game against Spain
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
FIBA has not specified what action will be taken against the
Nigerian.
</P>
<P>
It was the first positive drug test of the two-week World
 Basketball Championship.
</P>
<P>
Ephedrine is classed as a stimulant and is typically found in
 cold medications. Its use normally carries a warning or a ban of
 three months. 
