<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mogadishu Faction Leaders Reach Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The main faction leaders in
north Mogadishu, in their first face-to-face meeting, have
finally concluded a five-point deal over the long-awaited
formation of an administration in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
The meeting ended Thursday night was held between Ali Mahdi
Mohamed and his main rival within his faction, Dr Hussein Hsjji
Bod, with the attendance of south Mogadishu's main faction
leaders including Hussein Mohamed Aidid and Osman Ali Atto.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued at the end of the meeting, the
two sides had agreed upon the settlement of the difficulties
created by the different kinds of money circulating in Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
North Mogadishu people use the money known as Bal-yar printed
in 1992 during the civil war, while Bal-Weyn is used in the
South of the capital.
</P>
<P>
However, the two kinds of money are inter-changeable as money
dealers transfer them to benefit from their exchange rates as
they do to the hard currencies.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have also agreed to jointly name a technical
committee with the knowledge of law administration for the
completion of the regional laws.
</P>
<P>
The accord between Mahdi and Bod also includes the
establishment of Mogadishu's administration and the opening of
the airport and sea ports which remained out of use since 1995.
</P>
<P>
Another item also agreed upon is the reimposition of the
Islamic Sharia Law under the leadership of knowledgeable Moslem
scholars.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was a total success as it has brought about the
full collaboration of Mahdi and Bod over decision making for the
North Mogadishu faction, the technical and mediatory group from
both sides said.
</P>
<P>
However, even though many people have applauded the pact,
there are still hundreds of people who characterized it as just a
political joke.
</P>
<P>
One politician who asked to remain anonymous, noted that it is
impossible to settle the money difficulties until a government of
national unity is formed to unify the currency by collecting one
kind of money without damaging the economy.
</P>
<P>
However, many people have noticed that the joint nomination of
a new technical committee is significant for the completion of
Mogadishu's administration, as everything should be restarted
again from the very beginning.
</P>
<P>
As the politicians keep arguing over the formation of an
administration for the capital, the banditry activities and
lawlessness are increasing day by day, despite the formation of
an independent security force in several pockets of the capital
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The formation of a 100-strong security force had been agreed
upon by Mogadishu's business community in collaboration with the
gigantic telecommunications companies for the main Bakara market
and its surrounding areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980731.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
