<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Says That Farmers' Rights Need To Be Protected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Vice-Chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, Jiang
Chunyun, during a visit to Heilongjiang Province from July 25 to
31, said that farmers' rights and interests need to be better
protected to encourage their productive enthusiasm.
</P>
<P>
This is the most foundamental way to reach the country's
agricultural production goals, he said.
</P>
<P>
Many problems that occur in the countryside, Jiang said, should
be solved by implementing the Party's rural policies and by making
a greater effort to build a society of law in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
And, a greater effort should be made to increase public
awareness of the law among farmers and to get local officials and
law-enforcement departments to work in conformity with the law, he
said.
</P>
<P>
