<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister on New Guidelines Set for PLA Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Defense Minister Chi Haotian today
urged the People's Liberation Army (PLA) to keep pace with modern
military development trends and national reform, earnestly
implement the principles of military strategy in the new period,
and effectively increase defensive hi-tech combat capabilities.
</P>
<P>
General Chi, who is also member of the Political Bureau of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, vice-chairman of
the Central Military Commission, and state councillor, made the
remarks during the reception marking the PLA's 71st founding
anniversary today.
</P>
<P>
He said the army should achieve the target by accelerating
institutional and organizational restructuring and reform.
</P>
<P>
Chi said the whole army should proceed in accordance with the
principles of "downsizing, strengthening capabilities and
improving efficiency."
</P>
<P>
The PLA should work hard to further optimize its structure and
organization, while at the same time realigning relationships in
order to transform itself into an elite force well-versed in
advanced military theory, he noted. The PLA should strive to
attain an appropriate staffing level, reasonable structure and
efficient organization capable of providing effective logistical
support for highly trained and well-equipped officers and men with
a strict sense of discipline.
</P>
<P>
Chi underlined that the PLA units should attatch importance to
quality army-building, persevere in using science and technology
to achieve high-quality modernization and enhance military
capabilities. Moreover, he said, the army should pay great
attention to educating and training talented people and further
expand the program to greater expertise in high technology.
</P>
<P>
Noting that China is a staunch force for the maintenance of
regional and world peace, he said: "Its development is an
important contribution to human progress. We have resolutely and
continuously followed an independent foreign policy of peace, and
have all along pursued a defensive defense policy.
</P>
</TEXT>
