<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister on New Guidelines Set for PLA Development (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"We have always persevered in establishing and developing
friendly relations with all countries on the basis of the Five
Principles of Peaceful Co-existence. We have been active in
keeping contacts and cooperation with the armed forces of various
countries in the world and made unremitting efforts in promoting
world peace and development."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, to resolve the Taiwan question and
accomplish national reunification are the common aspirations of
the people of all ethnic groups in China, including the Taiwan
compatriots.
</P>
<P>
The PLA will continue to unswervingly adhere to the basic
guidelines of "peaceful reunification" and "one country, two
systems", and make its due contribution to promoting the great
cause of peaceful reunification of the motherland, Chi said.
</P>
