<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Bank Promises Six Billion Yuan More in Railway Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank (SDB)
has decided to grant more loans to railways by six billion
yuan this year, pushing the annual credit line for railways up to
22.27 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The SDB raised the loan quota for railways construction mainly
to echo the national call to increase support for the
infrastructure sector and thereby stimulate the economy, according
to SDB officials.
</P>
<P>
The increased loans will be used to meet the capital shortfalls
in railway construction involving some key railways projects such
as the Baocheng (Baoji-Chengdu) Double Track Railway, Nankun
(Nanning-Kunming) Railway, and Neikun Railway (Neijiang-Kunming).
</P>
<P>
The SDB has also utilized several ways to facilitate
project-appraisal work in order to ensure timely loans for key
projects. By the end of July, the bank had finished evaluating
nine railway projects and promised loans worth 24.58 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
As a policy-oriented bank supporting the infrastructure sector
and basic industries, the SDB has set its annual credit line at
122.8 billion yuan, up 11.6 percent from 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
