<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks End Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 30.04
points, or 0.38 percent, to close the week's trading at 7,936.20
points Friday.
</P>
<P>
The market's turnover was 3,700 million HK dollars (474 million
U.S. dollars), 370 million HK dollars (47 million U.S. dollars)
less than that of Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index plunged sharply during the first three
days of the week due to uncertainties in Japan's economic future
and other external factors. It suffered a total loss of 3.9
percent this week and has fluctuated between 7,900 and 8,000
since Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The HSI rebounded 97.33 points, or 1.25 percent, to close at
7,906.16 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It rose 74.19 points, or 0.94 percent, to open Friday's morning
trading at 7,980.35 but remained volatile during the day.
</P>
<P>
The index edged down 5.70 points, or 0.07 percent, to close at
7,900.46 at midday. 
</P>
