<HEADLINE> Jiujiang Prepares for Possible Heavy Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JIUJIANG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The city of Jiujiang in east
China's Jiangxi Province is building an emergency protective
shelter 24 meters high to prepare for the worst in order to
protect downtown areas and 400,000 local residents.
</P>
<P>
The city's primary Yangtze River levee faces an unprecedented
flood stage which has reached a record 23.02 meters today. The
levee stretches 17.64 km and has 84 floodgates less than 20 meters
tall. Eleven of the gates are known to have dangerous flaws.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu Province is also in the process of evacuating residents
on Yangtze River islands.
</P>
<P>
The province has 14 islands, which have 18,000 ha. of farmland
and are home to 370,000 people. The local government has already
evacuated over 20,000 islanders. 
</P>
