<HEADLINE> Two Taiwan Compatriots Kidnapped in Liaoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The public security department of
northeast China's Liaoning Province is now investigating the case
of two Taiwan compatriots who were kidnapped in Liaoning's
Haicheng city on Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
Wei Tein-kang, a Taiwan businessman who was kidnapped while on
a business trip in Liaoning, managed to escape and reported to the
local police after being held for two days.
</P>
<P>
Acting on information provided by Wei, the police conducted a
search and investigation and discovered that Lin Ti-chuan, the
other kidnapped Taiwanese, was dead in a hospital in Haicheng
yesterday. Doctors said Lin was already dead when she was brought
to the hospital.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary investigation shows that Wei, a deputy general
manager of a Taiwan trade company, maintains business connections
with a Haicheng company, and that Wei's company has owed more than
700,000 U.S. dollars to his Haicheng business partner since April.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of his business partner, Wei came to Dalian,
port city in Liaoning, with his girlfriend Lin Ti-chuan on
Monday. They were both kidnapped upon their arrival in Dalian.
</P>
<P>
Local police, already having some ideas about the
identification of the kidnapper suspects, are now searching for
them. The Ministry of Public Security has dispatched personnel to
Liaoning to supervize the investigation of the case.  
</P>
</TEXT>
