<HEADLINE> Guangzhou's Second Subway Line Under Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Work on the construction of the
Haizhu Square Station in Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province, began on July 28, marking the formal start of
the city's second subway line.
</P>
<P>
The second subway line, listed as one of Guangzhou's key
projects for the 1996-2000 period, was approved by the State
Development and Planning Commission this May. It's estimated
cost is 9.9 billion yuan, and more than 60 percent of the
construction equipment will be produced domestically.
</P>
<P>
The projected north-south subway line will start from the new
site of the Guangzhou Trade Fair for a total length of 21.34
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The new line will include 10.43 kilometers of subway, 10.03
kilometers of elevated line, a short transitional section, and 19
stations.
</P>
<P>
The second subway will join the first east-west line at Park
Front Station when completed. The new line is expected to handle
32,800 passengers during rush hours when completed.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the finishing touches are now being put on
the first subway line, which is expected to open to traffic by the
end of this year.
</P>
<P>
A 5.4-kilometer section of the 18.5-kilometer-long first subway
line, costing 13.8 billion yuan, has been operating on a trial
basis since June 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
