<HEADLINE> Samaranch Calls on Crisis Meeting on Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The president of International
Olympic Committee (IOC) Juan Antonio Samaranch Friday called on a
crisis executive board meeting for next month to discuss doping
issue in sport in Lausanne, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
A statement released by the IOC said the meeting will be held
on August 20 "with a single item on the agenda: the fight against
doping in sport."
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also discuss preparations for an
international conference on doping which would be held in January
in Lausanne, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The decision came amid the drug-plagued Tour de France,
whereas couples of teams and riders are under investigation and
six teams have pulled out of the race by now.
</P>
<P>
Samaranch caused more roars when he was quoted in a Spanish
newspaper as saying that the list of banned drugs authorized by
the IOC should be drastically reduced.
</P>
<P>
But the president denied that the IOC withdrew their stand in
fighting against doping in sport, reassuring that the IOC will
carry on their task against performance-enhancing drugs in the
2000 Olympic Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
