<HEADLINE> CAS to Build New Management Information System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences
(CAS) will establish a more efficient management information
system (MIS) which will operate through computer networks by the
year 2000, said the CAS president Lu Yongxiang today.
</P>
<P>
The CAS will spend 8.5 million yuan (about one-million
U.S. dollars) to build 15 comprehensive information systems and
management resources data banks, and ten management systems for
various departments, Lu told a CAS meeting on MIS in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The rest of the funds will be used in developing a multimedia
information exchange platform, introducing and upgrading the
software in management systems, and providing computer training
for the management staff, he said.
</P>
<P>
The new management system will provide modern methods for
decision-making and management at the CAS and help collect and
sort management resources data, Lu said, adding that it will also
help meet the statistics demands of state organizations.
</P>
<P>
The CAS has invested more than 100 million yuan (about 12 million
U.S. dollars) in the construction of information infrastructure
during the past two decades, and a computer network connecting
over 100 CAS research institutes has been established.
</P>
<P>
"We will pay special attention to the security of the new
management system, and try to prevent access by illegal users and
`hackers,'" Lu noted. He said the CAS will issue strict rules on
information protection and use advanced computer techniques to
prohibit illegal access. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
