<HEADLINE> Indian Government Runs Out of Steam: Congress Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Sonia Gandhi, president of
Congress, India's biggest opposition party, Friday stepped up her
attack on the BJP-led government, which, she asserted, has run out
of steam.
</P>
<P>
This is the second attack on the Vajpayee coalition government
by the Congress leader this week. She made her first attack on the
government when she addressed a massive rally of Congress workers
here on July 28.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting of national executive and state
presidents of the Indian Youth Congress, Sonia said the
government's five-month rule had resulted in a directional
paralysis as it had run out of steam intellectually, morally and
financially. She charged the Vajpayee government with failure on
all fronts, especially in containing the prices and maintaining
law and order.
</P>
<P>
Crime had reached alarming proportions and that even physical
security for the ordinary citizen has been in jeopardy. The rule
of the government has witnessed skyrocketing prices of essential
commodities and vegetables, she further said.
</P>
<P>
The Congress president asked the Youth Congress to launch a
campaign against the coalition government at the Center. 
</P>
