<HEADLINE> 105 Die in Flood, Landslide in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A total of 105 people have died
and four others are missing in flood and landslide across Nepal
since mid-April, press reports here said Friday.
</P>
<P>
When the Central Natural Calamity Rehabilitation Committee met
here Thursday, representatives from concerned government agencies
noted that the death toll went up due to lack of coordination
among government agencies and their poor preparedness for fighting
the disasters, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting stressed the need for coordination and awareness
generation to prevent natural calamities and decided that from the
new fiscal year which began in mid-July, each of the departments
concerned would maintain a separate budget for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
It also decided that preventive measures to reduce the impact
of calamities would be strengthened with research and studies on
possible calamities, the reports said. 
</P>
