<HEADLINE> TVM Withdraws from Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BRUSSELS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Dutch cycling team TVM
decided to pull out of the Tour de France cycle race, adding to
six the number that left the Tour, a Dutch news agency reported on
Friday in Amsterdam, the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The ANP news agency reported that the police raids on the team
hotel and allegations of drug-taking have driven the team out of
the race.
</P>
<P>
The team is expected to depart for the Netherlands on Friday.
</P>
