<HEADLINE> Singapore Stock Market Closes Marginally Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices ended Marginally
higher Friday as the benchmark Straits Times Industrial Index
(STII) inched up 4.67 points to close at 1,064.20.
</P>
<P>
Total volume was 163.29 million shares valued at 149.44 million
Singapore dollars (86.93 million U.S. dollars). Rises outnumbered
falls by 169 to 110 while 309 counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Frt Links was the most active stock as it finished on a
turnover of 15.29 million units. It was followed by Li Xin that
had 14.75 million counters done. PanpacMed was next with 8.00
million shares changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 remained the top gainer of the day as it climbed 80
cents to close at 21.00 Singapore dollars. KepFELS rose by 20
cents to close at 3.22 Singapore dollars. OUT was up 20 cents to
finish at 1.40 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, DBS was the biggest loser as it lost 15 cents
to close at 6.70 Singapore dollars. Ke Fin w01 shed 15 cents to
end at 0.07 Singapore dollars. HS went down 12 cents to finish at
4.30 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said shares ended the morning session moderately higher
on light bargaining hunting by foreign institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
They also said that the dispute between Singapore and Malaysia
over the relocation of a Malaysian Customs, Immigration and
Quarantine facility in Singapore weighed on the market sentiment.
</P>
