<HEADLINE> France's Unemployment Rate Drops To 11.8 Percent in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS,July 31 (Xinhua) -- France's unemployment rate dropped by
0.5 percent to 11.8 percent or 2,965,400 in June, said the
Ministry of Employment on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The unemployed is 14,000 lower than that of May with the rate
among young women dropping the most.
</P>
<P>
The number of jobless men and women above 25 both has dropped,
while that of men under 25 has risen.
</P>
<P>
The number of chronically unemployed also dropped by 0.8
percent to stand at 1,152,200.  
