<HEADLINE> Cargo Handled at Wellington Port Rises 8 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- the Port of Wellington
increased the amount of cargo it handled in the last financial
year by 8 percent despite the economic slowdown, a local newspaper
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Imports through the port were always strong, but there had
been good growth in exports in the year ending June 30, the
Evening Post said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the paper added, the value of overseas cargo handled
by New Zealand's sea and air ports also increased in the first
half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Though cargo loaded for export tumbled 20 percent in gross
weight to 8.3 million tons, its value was 2.8 percent higher at
11.3 billion NZ dollars (5.87 billion U.S. dollars) than in the
first half of l997.
</P>
<P>
Over the same period, cargo unloaded was 10.3 percent higher at
6.5 million tons, and 8.1 percent higher by value at 10.57 billion
NZ dollars (5.49 billion U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
