<HEADLINE> Seles, Williams Advance to Quarterfinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles of the United
States had no trouble to beat Anne-Gaelle Sidot of France, while
her compatriot Venus Williams struggled to enter the quarterfinals
at the Bank of the West tournament in Stanford, California, on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Seles, winner of 1990 and 1992 in this event, had six aces and
never lost her serve to crack Sidot in 6-3, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Williams, third seed, rallied from one set down to advance the
quarterfinals with a 4-6, 6-1, 6-0 victory over Corina Morariu,
who was one of Seles' teammates on the U.S. Fed Cup team in Spain.
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seeded Natasha Zvereva of Belarus and No. 7 Elena
Likhovtseva of Russia also reached the quarterfinals. 
</P>
