<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romanian FM Leaves For Albania For Solution to Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Foreign Minister Andrei
Plesu left here Friday for Tirana in an attempt to find a
political solution to the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
"When dramatic things occur among neighbors, it is normal and
it is a sign of good-neighborliness, civilization and humanity to
try to help," Plesu said at the airport before departure.
</P>
<P>
"The solution we are thinking of," Plesu added, "is the same
proposed by the international community," -- a political solution
in Kosovo as soon as possible, the Rompres news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The developments in Kosovo are a matter of deep concern for
Romania. Worrying about the possible extension of the conflict in
the region, it backs the international efforts in solving the
crisis through political means.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Plesu will also discuss with his hosts
Romania-Albania ties with an emphasis on strengthening
South-East European stability and security, the report added.
</P>
</TEXT>
