<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 09:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Shows Slight Downward Trend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Market exhibited
a slight downward tendency this week, while the turnover was
sustained at last week's level, a market report said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The market review issued by Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corporation Limited (CISCO) said the CISCO All-Share Index closed
on Thursday at 419.1 points, with a weekly decline of 6.7 points.
</P>
<P>
The review said that investor psychology and investment
strategies this year seem to largely be driven by island's
political factors which have become a major impediment to a
further rise in the stock market.
</P>
<P>
Tensions have escalated on the island since Cyprus signed a
deal with Russia in January 1997 to buy the S-300 anti-aircraft
missile system, which is scheduled to be deployed in Cyprus later
this year.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the review said the summer period which is by now
well under way, has traditionally proved an indolent period for
the stock market with the exception of the bull market run in
1989-90.
</P>
<P>
The total weekly turnover was 4.8 million Cyprus pounds (about
9.6 million U.S. dollars), up from 4.7 million pounds (about 9.4
million dollars) the previous week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
