<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiujiang People in Flood Control (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- His neighbors considered Deng
Yong, 10, to be nothing more than a mischievous boy up until
Thursday, when they commented that he had "grown up overnight".
</P>
<P>
Deng, a resident of suburban Jiujiang City in east China's
Jiangxi Province, also said that he has been "a personal sense of
maturation."
</P>
<P>
Continuous rains over the past few days eased somewhat on
Thursday evening, providing Deng and his friends an opportunity to
go for a swim in a nearby river.
</P>
<P>
A short time later, however, the frolicking youngsters heard
the distant shouts of a person maintaining vigil on the river
dike. "I listened closely and heard the man say leaks had been
detected in nearby culverts and most men in the village kilometers
away are loading dirt to reinforce the dikes," Deng said. He
emphasized his statement with hand gestures.
</P>
<P>
The young men immediately returned to their village and joined
their mothers and sisters in collecting quilts to temporarily
patch cracks in the culverts.
</P>
<P>
"The quilts failed to stop the leaks, so we used sandbags as
reinforcement," said Deng. "We had to drag the heavy bags, but
managed to plug the leak in about an hour."
</P>
<P>
"The simple fact was that we would have been left homeless had
the embankments collapsed. This prompted me to forget my age and
join in the battle against flooding," said the young man.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980731.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiujiang People in Flood Control (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xia Jing, the female manager of a local bathhouse, and 50
female employees joined in the efforts to construct a new
cofferdam to ease pressure on a floodgate.
</P>
<P>
Xia, 22, contributed relief supplies and the use of vehicles
and equipment with an estimated value of 10,000 yuan. "I'll do
everything I can to help," she said.
</P>
<P>
A family of four also participated in the effort. The
wife and daughther hurriedly filled sandbags with crushed stones,
with the husband carrying the heavy bag to the floodgate.
</P>
<P>
"That's my wife and daughther, and my son's transporting stones,"
said the weary man as he wiped sweat from his dripping brow. "My
entire family is helping to protect the floodgate."
</P>
<P>
The couple erected a themporary shelter near the floodgate a
month earlier. "We have maintained a constant vigil in case of an
unexpected emergency," said his wife Yang Sijin.
</P>
<P>
"We prepare meals at home, and bring them to our parents. The
one-way trip takes about half an hour," according to their
daughther Yu Yangbao.
</P>
<P>
"Temporary losses are unimportant. The most important thing is
to prothect the floodgate," said Yang.
</P>
<P>
The family estimates its expenditures in the effort have
exceeded 20,000 yuan. The husband explained that wealthier people
should pay their just dues to society. "The flood control effort
has reached critical point and we simply can't wait for the
government to allocathe relief funds," her husband said . Endithem

