<HEADLINE> Shanghai Diesel Engines Introduced in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Diesel Engine Company
(SDEC) of China Friday gave a product introductory briefing here
to introduce its products, aiming at expanding its export to the
Myanmar market.
</P>
<P>
The introductory ceremony was attended by Second Secretary of
the Myanmar State Peace and Development Council (SPDC) Lieutenant
General Tin Oo, SPDC Third Secretary Lieutenant General Win
Myint, Minister of Industry-2 Major General Hla Myint Swe, Yangon
Mayor U Ko Lay and other Myanmar officials as well as Economic and
Commercial Councilor Lin Jian of the Chinese Embassy here.
</P>
<P>
Different models of diesel engines produced by the Shanghai
company for powering various kinds of construction machinery,
heavy duty trucks, marine vessels, generating sets and
agricultural machinery were introduced at the briefing.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai diesel engines entered the Myanmar market in 1991.
After 1996, its exports to the country reached several hundred
units annually.
</P>
<P>
Users in Myanmar welcome these products for good quality and
favorable price.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Diesel Engine Company grew out of Shanghai Diesel
Engine Works which was founded in 1947 and restructured as a stock
company in 1993.
</P>
<P>
It is also the first company in China's internal combustion
engine industry to passed the international quality certification
of ISO9001. Its products are exported to more than 40 countries
and regions. 
</P>
