<HEADLINE> Israeli Soldier Killed in Southern Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 31 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli soldier was killed
and five others injured Thursday in a heavy change of fire with
Hezbollah guerrillas in southern Lebanon, Israel Radio confirmed
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers were on their way to a routine practice when
ambushed by Hezbollah guerrillas, who opened fire with heavy
machine guns and mortars. The Israeli force returned fire.
</P>
<P>
Israel's military helicopters evacuated injured soldiers to
hospital, but doctors tried unsuccessfully to save a 21-year-old
soldier.
</P>
<P>
The death brought to nine the number of Israeli soldiers
killed so far this year in the 15-kilometer deep security zone
in southern Lebanon which was set up in 1985 by Israel after
it withdrew the bulk of a 1982 invasion force.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, is spearheading
a war of attrition against 1,500 Israeli troops and their ally,
the 2,500-strong South Lebanon Army militia. 
</P>
