<HEADLINE> URGENT: SAARC Summit Ends, Adopting Declaration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The 10th summit of the
seven-member South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation
(SAARC) closed here Friday after the adoption of the Colombo
Declaration.
</P>
<P>
The sections of the Declaration include political cooperation,
economic cooperation, poverty in South Asia, terrorism and drugs,
women and children and international political developments.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan President Chandrika Kumaragunga said in her closing
address that the leaders at their three-day summit discussed and
arrived at "very concrete and positive decisions" on issues under
consideration.
</P>
<P>
The next SAARC summit will be held in Kathmandu, Nepal, in
1999.
</P>
<P>
SAARC, which groups Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives,
Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka, was formed in 1985 with its main
objective being to accelerate economic growth and social
development in member states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
