<HEADLINE> China's Injured Gymnast Moved to New Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Sang Lan, who injured her spinal
cord on July 21 at the current Goodwill Games, has been
transferred to a new hospital in Manhattan this morning.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old Chinese vaulting champion, who had an operation
three days ago, arrived at the Mt. Sinai Rehabilitation Institute
near the Central Park this morning.
</P>
<P>
"She was in a high spirit. She loves the new hospital and the
new room," said Tu Mingde, head of the Chinese delegation.
</P>
<P>
Mt. Sinai is one of the few model spinal cord injury centers in
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Sang Lan's parents chose the center for the next phase of her
treatment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
