<HEADLINE> Brazilians, Americans Win Beach Volleyball Matches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Top seeds Shelda Bede and Adriana
Behar of Brazil beat their rivals to win a Group B match in the
women's beach volleyball competition at the 1998 Goodwill Games
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian pair beat Pauline Manser and Kerri Pottarst of
Australia 15-9.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Karolyn Kirby and Liz Masakayan of the
United States sailed into the next round easily after thrashing
Kristine Drakich and Guylaine Dumont of Canada 15-5 in Group A.
</P>
<P>
In the other two matches, second-seeded Lisa Arce and McPeak of
the United States defeated Eva Dosoudilova and Sona Celbova of the
Czech Republic 15-9, while Italy's Laura Bruschini and Annamarie
Solazzi beat Germans Maile Friedrichsen and Danja Musch 15-10.
</P>
<P>
The medal round competition will start Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
