<DOCNO> XIE19980731.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy, Mexican Ministers Discuss EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini met Mexican Foreign Minister Rosario Green on Wednesday to
discuss relations between Mexico and the European Union, the ANSA
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
They talked about how to further improve bilateral relations in
the political, economic, commercial, cultural, and scientific
sectors, in light of the accords forged between the European Union
and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The accords, signed on December 8, 1997, aim at promoting
political dialogue and economic cooperation between Mexico and the
EU, and must be ratified by the parliaments of EU countries.
</P>
<P>
Also on the table were: reform of the United Nations Security
Council, the U.N. itself, the institution of the International
Criminal Court, and the Euro-Latin American Summit called for June
1999.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed Latin America-United States relations
regarding Cuba.
</P>
<P>
They highlighted the close economic relations between Mexico
and Italy. Mexico is Italy's third largest trade partner in Latin
America.
</P>
<P>
Both Dini and Green agreed to strengthen economic relations
through direct investment, small and medium businesses, and
training programs.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers expressed their willingness to enhance
cooperation between the two countries in fighting drug
trafficking, judicial procedures and extradition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
