<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Yin Claims 3,000m Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese runner Yin Lili captured the
gold medal in the women's 3,000 meters at the World Junior
Athletics Championships in Annecy, France, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Yin Lili rocketed her paces from the final two laps, leading
the rest of the field to win the title with a time of eight
minutes 57.09 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's Yimenshu Taye, the world cross country junior
champion, finished second in 9:01.70.
</P>
<P>
However, an officiating mistake with the lap counter showed
that Kenya's Salim Kipsang, who was trying to grab the gold medal
with his team-mate Benson Barus, stopped running with one lap to
go.
</P>
<P>
Barus, who admitted he had not been looking at the device and
only listening for the bell to sound, clocked in 29 minutes 24.28
seconds for the title, while Kipsang was confused about what to do.
</P>
<P>
Kipsang recovered his composure quickly to secure the silver
medal in 29:36.80.
</P>
<P>
Hungary's Zoltan Kovago won the men's discus title with the
last throw of the competition at 59.36 meters.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 10,000 meters walking, Russia's Roman Rasskazov
won in 41:55.95, followed by China's Liu Yunfeng, China in the
second place in 42:01.11.
</P>
<P>
Mario Flores of Mexico carried home the bronze medal, clocking
42:04.55. 
</P>
</TEXT>
