<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dual Mode Paging Network Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A dual mode paging network, the
first of its kind in China, went into operation earlier this week
in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The network consists of radio paging combined with computer
network and features an interactive mobile digital technology for
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The network, jointly operated by the Shanghai Guomai
Telecommunications Co. Ltd. and U.S.-based General Wireline
Communications, offers improved paging functions and carry short
information stories edited and sent by customers. The network's
pager units offer 20 functions.
</P>
<P>
The companies established cooperative ties in 1995, and
introduced an experimental network in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
