<HEADLINE> United States Upset by Lithuania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion the United
States were upset by Lithuania 84-82 in group C at World
Basketball Championship on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The American coach Rudy Tomjanovic said his team lost partly
because they had underestimated their opponents.
</P>
<P>
"My players should be more serious and not underestimate their
opponents," said Tomjanovic.
</P>
<P>
"I hope this defeat will wake us up and eventually do us good,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Arturas Karnisovas led the Lithuanian scorers with 29 points,
followed by Saulius Stombergasd with 15 and Jonas Kazlauskas with
12.
</P>
<P>
The Americans, who trailed Lithuania 47-34 at halftime, rallied
strongly in the second half.
</P>
<P>
Jimmy Oliver finished the match with 18 points. Michael Hawkins
contributed 16 and Jason Sasser added 13.
</P>
<P>
In another group C match, Brazil hammered down the resistance
from a strenuous South Korean team to win 76-73.
</P>
<P>
South Korean Min Sang Lee led both sides by scoring 19 points.
His team added 18 while Min Kyung Yang had 16.
</P>
<P>
Caio Cazziolato was the top Brazilian scorer with 17, followed
by Rogerio Klafke with 14 and Joao Jose Vianna 12.
</P>
<P>
In group A, Frangiskos Alvertis scored 18 points to help hosts
Greece came from behind to beat Italy 64-56.
</P>
<P>
The Greeks had trailed 39-35 at halftime but fought back to
lead 49-41 with 10 minutes left.
</P>
<P>
But the Italians, led by Gregor Fucka who finished the game
with 19 points, rallied and went ahead 56-55.
</P>
<P>
Panayotis Fassoulas scored a vital score in the last minute to
go ahead again and the victory was in their hands when Italy had a
three-pointer disallowed.
</P>
<P>
In the other group A game, Canada defeated Senegal 70-57.
</P>
<P>
In Group D, Spain squeezed out a 77-76 victory over Australia,
with forward Alberto Herreros scoring 24 points.
</P>
<P>
Australia now have suffered two straight defeats and must beat
Nigeria. on Friday to qualify for the next round.
</P>
<P>
The Australians wasted their chance to win the game when center
Paul Rogers missed a five-meter shot with less than a second to go.
</P>
<P>
Forward Tony Ronaldson was Australia's leading scorer with 17
points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
