upset in the third round as he was stunned by Nicolas Lapentti of
Ecuador, No. 62nd in the world, in 6-4, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, another former French Open champion, was the top
seed left after Marcelo Rios of Chile pulled out with an injury.
</P>
