<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Province Increasing Export of Agricultural Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- An increasing number and variety
of agricultural products from central China's Henan Province are
being exported overseas, with total trade volume hitting nearly
700 million U.S. dollars by June this year.
</P>
<P>
This increase is mostly attributed to the mushrooming of local
facilities for agricultural exports such as bases for seeds in
Xinyang, Luohe and Luoyang, aquatic products in southern parts of
the province, fruits and edible fungus in western parts of Henan,
and flower-growing in Xuchang and Luoyang.
</P>
<P>
In addition to primary items, local exports of processed
agricultural products such as canned food and fodder are rising
sharply.
</P>
<P>
Henan has expanded its exports to a greater number of countries
and regions including the ROK, Southeast Asia, Britain, the United
States, and Germany, along with the traditional destinations of
Japan, Russia, Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to further improve its export range and
increase the export of livestock, farm and sideline products,
especially meat, fur and wool, and exports green and healthy food.
</P>
<P>
Local seeds are now exported to a dozen countries and region.
</P>
<P>
One of the country's leading producers of agricultural
products, Henan contributes a great deal to China's output of
wheat, cotton and oil-bearing crops.
</P>
<P>
The use of more than 64 million U.S. dollars of overseas
investment for local agriculture is also helping boost the growth
of related exports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980731.0237 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Grain Prices Up In Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Grain prices in Henan Province,
a leading producer in central China, have stopped their downward
movement, according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The price of a kg of both wheat and corn was 1.2 yuan on
average since the end of June, 7.1 percent more for wheat and 0.8
percent more for corn than a month ago.
</P>
<P>
This is related to the nationwide reform of the grain marketing
system organized by the State Council, a provincial agriculture
official says.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government asked all parts of the province to
implement the central government policy of purchasing all grain
sold to the state at a negotiable price and putting a bottom
purchase price on grain as a protective measure. Both prices are
higher than the market price, and in this way, state-owned grain
departments have some control over grain.
</P>
<P>
However, agriculture analysts think the grain price is still
not high enough to offset state subsidized purchases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980731.0238 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Results of Croatia Open Tennis Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Following are the results of the
400,000 U.S. dollars Croatia Open tournament in Umag, Croatia on
Thursday (prefix number denotes seeding):
