<HEADLINE> U.S. Win World Women's Softball Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The United States won their fifth
straight world title by edging Australia 1-0 in the final of the
Women's Softball Championships in Fujinomiya, Japan, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rain and thunder had delayed the match after Lisa
Fernandez helped the Americans a 1-0 lead at the top of the first
inning over the Atlanta bronze medallists.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Thursday the Americans whitewashed Japan 4-0, helped
by Sheila Douty's two-run homer in the first inning before earning
a place against Australia in the final.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese had to be satisfied with the bronze medal.
</P>
<P>
Atlanta Olympic silver medallists China finished fourth after
they lost to Japan 0-3 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Canada was fifth after beating European champions Italy 1-0 an
d snatched the ticket to the Sydney Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The United States, Australia, Japan and China also qualified
for the 2000 Games.
</P>
<P>
It was the first qualifying event for the Olympics. The top
four countries except Australia, who are eligible as the hosts,
earned a berth in the Olympics after the 11-day competition.
</P>
