<HEADLINE> Panama City Collects Guns for Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A large collection of firearms
has been handed in to a municipality of the Panama District, in a
program named "Arms for Food."
</P>
<P>
In the municipality of San Miguelito, a total of 108 weapons
was delivered to the government in exchange for food bonuses, home
appliances, and building materials, Mayor Felipe Cano of Panama
City told reporters on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The "Arms for Food" program, which started on March 12 and
ended on July 23 in that municipality, won support from private
sectors and the national government.
</P>
<P>
Most of the weapons were handed in by heads of households who
expressed their approval of the program, Mayor Cano said.
</P>
<P>
The Panama Province Governance initiated the program in urban
areas of this capital city at the end of last year, and it will be
continued throughout the city this year.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the project is to reduce crime, especially
before the referendum for presidential re-election of the
Republic, which is scheduled for August 30. 
</P>
