<HEADLINE> More Than A Quarter of Registered Factories Close in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 31 (Xinhua) -- More than a quarter of registered
factories in Thailand closes and nearly 35,000 people lost their
jobs during the first half of this year, according to the
Industrial Work Department of the Thai government available
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The department said that 1,330 of 4,543 registered factories
closed and 34,892 out of 158,995 workers lost their jobs.
</P>
<P>
the statistics do not include factories not registered with
the department. If those were taken into account, the number of
closed factories could be up to four times as high and extent of
unemployment even more distressing, a department official was
quoted Friday by the Bangkok post as saying.
</P>
<P>
The closures wiped out 9.9 billion baht (247.5 million U.S.
dollars) of industrial investment totaling 250 billion baht (6.25
billion U.S. dollars), the department estimated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
