<HEADLINE> Third Yangtze Flood Crest Passes Jiujiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JIUJIANG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The third Yangtze River flood
crest passed Jiujiang safely at 3 am this morning, with the water
level rising to 23.02 meters, 0.8 meters higher than the
record high.
</P>
<P>
At 8 am this morning, the water level dropped to 22.96 meters,
but still higher than the danger mark, according the Flood Control
Headquarters of Jiujiang city, Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The smooth passing didn't mean that the flooding is over,
because the high water level along the 196-kilometer Yangtze
section in the city will hold for some time. To lift the state of
emergency, another drop of 2.66 meters is needed.
</P>
<P>
Now, 400,000 civilians and soldiers and officers are still
working on the embankments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
