<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Indonesia's Irian Jaya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.9 on the
Richter scale struck Indonesia's Irian Jaya Province Thursday,
according to reports reaching here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The quake hit Jayawijaya district in the eastern part of the
province at 3:05 a.m., with its epicenter traced at 113 kilometers
north of Wamena and 45 kilometers beneath the earth's surface.
</P>
<P>
There was no report of casualty, an official of the
meteorological and geophysical station said.
</P>
<P>
Jayawijaya is prone to earthquakes. Small quakes jolt the
district almost every year. The last powerful earthquake that
rocked the district was in 1989, when hundreds of people were
buried in landslides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
