<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chen Xitong Sentenced to 16 Years' Imprisonment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Municipal Higher
People's Court this morning sentenced Chen Xitong, former
secretary of the Beijing Municipal Committee of the Communist Party
of China, to 16 years' imprisonment on the charges of corruption
and dereliction of duty.
</P>
<P>
The sentence was pronounced in a public court session. The
verdict says Chen was sentenced to 13 years' imprisonment on the
charge of corruption and to four years' imprisonment on the charge
of dereliction of duty. In combination, Chen will serve 16 years'
imprisonment. The bribes Chen accepted should be confiscated and
handed over to the State Treasury, the court verdict adds.
</P>
<P>
The verdict of the Beijing Municipal Higher People's Court is a
judgment of first instance. According to the country's Criminal
Procedural Law, if Chen disagrees with the verdict, he can appeal
to the Supreme People's Court within 10 days beginning on the next
day after the verdict of first instance is made. 
</P>
</TEXT>
