<HEADLINE> Kabbah Appeals for More Aid to His Country's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Alhaji Ahmad Kabbah, the
President of the Republic of Sierra Leone, on Thursday appealed
to the international community for more aid to his conntry's
reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Special United Nations Conference on Sierra
Leone held Thursday, President Kabbah said, "peace and security
should be considered in the context of our capacity to pursue and
achieve. Our plans for reconstruction and long-term economic
recovery are attainable. But we cannot talk about peace-building
without reference to the material elements."
</P>
<P>
"The Monitoring Group established by the Economic Community of
West African States (ECOMOG) has continued its objective of
restoring peace and security in those parts of the country where
the rebels and remnants of the junta continue to operate," the
president said.
</P>
<P>
"ECOMOG has been experiencing logistics and related problems
in its efforts to rid the affected areas of those destructive
elements, and to restore normal community life there," he told
the conference.
</P>
<P>
Kabbah said thus there was an urgent need for additional
material and logistics support for ECOMOG and for the
deployment of observes working with ECOMO.
</P>
<P>
The President said he feared that unless assistance for
ECOMOG was forthcoming, the rebel activities will not only
continue and create more human tragedy, but will also drain the
country's limited resources.
</P>
<P>
Kabbah added that the poor conditions of the roads, bridges and
social infrastructures such as school, administrative and health
facilities in the rural areas of the country, have greatly
deterred progress in establishing normal lives in those areas,
and have seriously compromised the Country's capacity to
resettle refugees and the displaced.
</P>
<P>
The Special United Nations Conference on Sierra Leone is
convened to address the problems facing the country's
reconstruction and rehabilitation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
