<HEADLINE> IDB Finances Argentine Program for Children at Risk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) Thursday announced the approval of 30 million U.S.
dollars in financing in national currency for Argentina to support
a program for children at risk.
</P>
<P>
The financing will be used to create a vast network to provide
services to tens of thousands of children and teenagers at social
risk.
</P>
<P>
The program, which involves the public sector and civil society
groups such as nongovernmental organizations and religious, social
or neighborhood associations, will finance projects to assist
children and adolescents in 19 participating provinces and
jurisdictions in the country.
</P>
<P>
The IDB funding consists of a loan for the equivalent in pesos
of 10 million dollars from the bank's ordinary capital, another
loan for the same amount from the Bank's Fund for Special
Operation (FSO) and a grant for the equivalent in pesos of 10
million dollars from the FSO's net income pool. Apart from the IDB
funding, local counterpart contributes total 13.3 million dollars.
</P>
