<HEADLINE> S. Africa Ratifies SADC Anti-Drug Protocol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 30 (Xinhua) -- South Africa Wednesday
deposited its instrument of ratification of an anti-drug protocol
of the Southern African Development Community (SADC) at the SADC
headquarters in Gaborone, Botswana, the Foreign Ministry said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The objectives of the protocol are to reduce and eventually
eliminate drug trafficking, money laundering, corruption and the
illicit use and abuse of drugs through cooperation among
enforcement agencies," the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
So far, six of the 16 SADC member states have ratified the
document while other countries are believed to follow suit soon,
the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It said the protocol was a joint venture of the SADC and the
European Union, which was also the sole donor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
